parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among different requests. The client token can contain only ASCII characters.

>  If you do not set this parameter, the system uses **RequestId** as **ClientToken**. **RequestId** may be different for each API request.

parameters.name: NetworkAclId
parameters.description: The ID of the network ACL.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The region where the network ACL is deployed. You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: SourceNetworkAclId
parameters.description: The ID of the network ACL whose rules you want to copy.
